            64,
            129,
            188,
            248,
            302,
            359
          ],
          "text": "I do not know how fast it is to construct this, but it may well be much faster than what I am doing now. If not, it still may be a good idea to construct the db of bboxes once and keep it updated. When any object’s bbox changes, we recalc only its edges in the graph. Then we still need to rebuild the component_map. Or, we could experiment with only tracing out a single component. Gemini recommends",
          "uuid": "9e9c80ec"
        }
      ]
    },
