          ],
          "text": "When an object is added to or removed from the scene, we can use the boost code to update the graph. Removed objects can either be actually removed or simply given a null bbox. That way, renumbering can be avoided or performed only once the fraction of null bboxes reaches some threshold. We would have a bidirectional map between vertex numbers and NodeIDs.",
          "uuid": "e98615b8"
        }
      ]
    },
